Description: Wall sherd of East Greek (North Ionian?) pottery cup or bowl; interior glazed with two red lines on lower wall; reserved outside save broad band painted on lower wall; inscription in reserved zone.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), temenos (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.362)
